# Intelligent Multi-Device Energy Management System

Full-stack web app using **FastAPI + HTML/CSS/JS** with Classical Planning and Decision Networks.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Frontend<br/>HTML/CSS/JS"] -->|REST API| B["FastAPI Backend"]
    B --> C["Planning Engine"]
    B --> D["Decision Network"]
    B --> E["Visualization<br/>matplotlib → PNG"]
```

## Scenario: Hospital ICU

| Device | Priority | Init Battery | Consumption | Charge Rate |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Ventilator | Critical (5) | 40% | 15/step | 25/step |
| Patient Monitor | High (4) | 60% | 10/step | 20/step |
| Infusion Pump | High (4) | 35% | 12/step | 20/step |
| Defibrillator | Medium (3) | 80% | 8/step | 18/step |
| Diagnostic Scanner | Low (1) | 70% | 5/step | 15/step |

**Constraints:** Max 2 simultaneous charges, horizon 5 steps, P(success) = 0.9, switching penalty = 5

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — FastAPI

#### [NEW] [main.py](file:///Users/raghunandanshaji/Downloads/AI%20Mini%20Proj/main.py)
FastAPI server with endpoints:
- `GET /` — Serve the frontend
- `POST /api/run` — Accept device config + parameters, run planning engine, return results JSON
- `GET /api/visualizations/{name}` — Serve generated matplotlib PNG charts
- Static file serving for frontend assets

#### [NEW] [planning_engine.py](file:///Users/raghunandanshaji/Downloads/AI%20Mini%20Proj/planning_engine.py)
Core AI logic:
- `Device` dataclass (name, priority, battery, consumption_rate, charge_rate)
- `State` — tuple of battery levels
- `forward_search()` — Generate all charging schedules via state-space search
- `compute_expected_utility()` — EU calculation with probabilistic success/failure
- `find_optimal_plan()` — Evaluate and rank all plans

#### [NEW] [visualizations.py](file:///Users/raghunandanshaji/Downloads/AI%20Mini%20Proj/visualizations.py)
Matplotlib chart generation (saved as PNGs):
1. Battery evolution over time (all devices, optimal plan highlighted)
2. State-space search tree (2–3 step subset)
3. Expected Utility comparison bar chart
4. Device-wise battery stability heatmap
5. Failure risk analysis chart

---

### Frontend — HTML/CSS/JS

#### [NEW] [static/index.html](file:///Users/raghunandanshaji/Downloads/AI%20Mini%20Proj/static/index.html)
Single-page app with sections:
1. **Hero/Landing** — Animated title, glowing effects, project intro
2. **Device Configuration** — Interactive cards for each device (editable battery, priority, rates)
3. **Parameters Panel** — Sliders for horizon, max charging slots, success probability, switching penalty
4. **Run Button** — Triggers planning with loading animation
5. **Results Dashboard** — Optimal plan display, EU score, plan details
6. **Visualizations Gallery** — Embedded charts with smooth reveal animations
7. **Analysis Section** — Insights, risk assessment, recommendations

#### [NEW] [static/styles.css](file:///Users/raghunandanshaji/Downloads/AI%20Mini%20Proj/static/styles.css)
Premium dark-mode design:
- Glassmorphism cards, gradient backgrounds, neon accents
- Smooth transitions, hover effects, scroll animations
- Responsive grid layout, custom sliders/inputs
- Loading spinner with pulse animation

#### [NEW] [static/script.js](file:///Users/raghunandanshaji/Downloads/AI%20Mini%20Proj/static/script.js)
- Fetch API calls to backend
- DOM manipulation for dynamic results rendering
- Scroll-triggered reveal animations (IntersectionObserver)
- Interactive device card editing
- Chart gallery with fade-in transitions

